title: ANGELS: Claim OF Todd Cunningham from Braves
text:
BY JEFF FLETCHER / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 9, 2015 Updated: 7:23 p.m. ANGELS: Claim OF Todd Cunningham from Braves Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» The Angels claimed outfielder Todd Cunningham on waivers from the Atlanta Braves, the first roster move since new general manager Billy Eppler took over the club on Monday.
Cunningham, 26, hit .223 with a .277 on-base percentage in 101 plate appearances in the majors in 2013 and 2015. Cunningham is a switch hitter who has played all three outfield positions, mostly center field in the minors.
Cunningham is out of options, but the Angels could still keep him if they can slip him through waivers.
